 <br>
IF I AM PULLING<br>
1)pull with bow<br>
<br>
2)when back at camp kick/disarm/autoattack<br>
<br>
3)wait for slow to land then taunt/kick/disarm until I have aggro<br>
<br>
4)Once aggro is established don’t taunt till mob turns away<br>
<br>
IF SOMEONE ELSE IS PULLING<br>
1)Tag with bow on inc<br>
<br>
2)(if high aggro puller-bard, pally,sk) taunt/kick/disarm/autoattack to get higher on aggro list than the puller (piggyback)<br>
<br>
3)Taunt/kick/disarm after slow lands<br>
<br>
4)Once aggro is established don’t taunt till mob turns away<br>
<br>
So far this seems to work ok.  People still have to watch there aggro but atleast it gives me a shot at keeping the mob on me.  Im curious what other tricks seem to work for people.  I group mostly in PoV/PoS and sometimes in CoD.  I realize this stuff can be found in several threads but i would like to see it all in one thread and maby stickyed.<br>
